 *
 *  @author  Martin Odersky
 *  @version 1.0
 */

  // IDE hooks
  def (Typers.this.Context)Typers.this.TypernewTyper(Typers.this.Contextcontext: Typers.this.ContextContext): Typers.this.TyperTyper = Typers.this.NormalTypernew Typers.this.NormalTyperNormalTyper(Typers.this.Contextcontext)

  /** when in 1.4 mode the compiler accepts and ignores useless
   *  type parameters of Java generics
   */
  def => BooleanonePointFourMode = Boolean(true)true // todo changeto: settings.target.value == "jvm-1.4"

  // Mode constants

  /** The three mode <code>NOmode</code>, <code>EXPRmode</code>
   *  and <code>PATTERNmode</code> are mutually exclusive.
   */
  val IntNOmode        = Int(0)0x000
  val IntEXPRmode      = Int(1)0x001
  val IntPATTERNmode   = Int(2)0x002
  val IntTYPEmode      = Int(4)0x004
 
  /** The mode <code>SCCmode</code> is orthogonal to above. When set we are
   *  in the this or super constructor call of a constructor.
   */
  val IntSCCmode       = Int(8)0x008

  /** The mode <code>FUNmode</code> is orthogonal to above.
   *  When set we are looking for a method or constructor.
   */
  val IntFUNmode       = Int(16)0x010

  /** The mode <code>POLYmode</code> is orthogonal to above.
   *  When set expression types can be polymorphic.
   */
  val IntPOLYmode      = Int(32)0x020

  /** The mode <code>QUALmode</code> is orthogonal to above. When set
   *  expressions may be packages and Java statics modules.
   */
  val IntQUALmode      = Int(64)0x040

  /** The mode <code>TAPPmode</code> is set for the function/type constructor
   *  part of a type application. When set we do not decompose PolyTypes.
   */
  val IntTAPPmode      = Int(128)0x080

  /** The mode <code>SUPERCONSTRmode</code> is set for the <code>super</code>
   *  in a superclass constructor call <code>super.&lt;init&gt;</code>.
   */
  val IntSUPERCONSTRmode = Int(256)0x100

  /** The mode <code>SNDTRYmode</code> indicates that an application is typed
   *  for the 2nd time. In that case functions may no longer be coerced with
   *  implicit views.
   */
  val IntSNDTRYmode    = Int(512)0x200

  /** The mode <code>LHSmode</code> is set for the left-hand side of an
   *  assignment.
   */
  val IntLHSmode       = Int(1024)0x400

  /** The mode <code>REGPATmode</code> is set when regular expression patterns
   *  are allowed. 
   */
  val IntREGPATmode    = Int(4096)0x1000

  /** The mode <code>ALTmode</code> is set when we are under a pattern alternative */
  val IntALTmode       = Int(8192)0x2000
  
  /** The mode <code>HKmode</code> is set when we are typing a higher-kinded type
   * adapt should then check kind-arity based on the prototypical type's kind arity
   * type arguments should not be inferred
   */
  val IntHKmode        = Int(16384)0x4000 // @M: could also use POLYmode | TAPPmode 

  /** The mode <code>JAVACALLmode</code> is set when we are typing a call to a Java method
   *  needed temporarily for vararg conversions
   *  !!!VARARG-CONVERSION!!!
   */
  val IntJAVACALLmode  = Int(32768)0x8000

  /** The mode <code>TYPEPATmode</code> is set when we are typing a type in a pattern
   */
  val IntTYPEPATmode   = Int(65536)0x10000

  private val IntstickyModes: IntInt  = => IntEXPRmode (Int)Int| => IntPATTERNmode (Int)Int| => IntTYPEmode (Int)Int| => IntALTmode

  private def (Int)IntfunMode(Intmode: IntInt) = Intmode (Int)Int& (=> IntstickyModes (Int)Int| => IntSCCmode) (Int)Int| => IntFUNmode (Int)Int| => IntPOLYmode

  private def (Int)InttypeMode(Intmode: IntInt) = 
    Intif ((Intmode (Int)Int& (=> IntPATTERNmode (Int)Int| => IntTYPEPATmode)) (Int)Boolean!= Int(0)0) => IntTYPEmode (Int)Int| => IntTYPEPATmode
    else => IntTYPEmode

  private def (Typers.this.global.Tree,Int)IntargMode(Typers.this.global.Treefun: Typers.this.global.TreeTree, Intmode: IntInt) =
    Intif (object Typers.this.global.treeInfotreeInfo.(Typers.this.global.treeInfo.trees.Tree)BooleanisSelfOrSuperConstrCall(Typers.this.global.Treefun)) Intmode (Int)Int| => IntSCCmode 
    else Intif (Typers.this.global.Treefun.=> Typers.this.global.Symbolsymbol (Long)BooleanhasFlag Long(1048576L)JAVA) Intmode (Int)Int| => IntJAVACALLmode // !!!VARARG-CONVERSION!!!
    else Intmode

    /** Would tree be a stable (i.e. a pure expression) if the type
     *  of its symbol was not volatile?
     */
    private def (Typers.this.global.Tree)BooleanisStableExceptVolatile(Typers.this.global.Treetree: Typers.this.global.TreeTree) = {
      Typers.this.global.Treetree.=> BooleanhasSymbol (Boolean)Boolean&& Typers.this.global.Treetree.=> Typers.this.global.Symbolsymbol (AnyRef)Boolean!= object Typers.this.global.NoSymbolNoSymbol (Boolean)Boolean&& Typers.this.global.Treetree.=> Typers.this.global.Typetpe.=> BooleanisVolatile (Boolean)Boolean&&

    /** Perform the following adaptations of expression, pattern or type `tree' wrt to 
     *  given mode `mode' and given prototype `pt':
     *  (-1) For expressions with annotated types, let AnnotationCheckers decide what to do
     *  (0) Convert expressions with constant types to literals
     *  (1) Resolve overloading, unless mode contains FUNmode 
     *  (2) Apply parameterless functions
     *  (3) Apply polymorphic types to fresh instances of their type parameters and
     *      store these instances in context.undetparams, 
     *      unless followed by explicit type application.
     *  (4) Do the following to unapplied methods used as values:
     *  (4.1) If the method has only implicit parameters pass implicit arguments
     *  (4.2) otherwise, if `pt' is a function type and method is not a constructor,
     *        convert to function by eta-expansion,
     *  (4.3) otherwise, if the method is nullary with a result type compatible to `pt'
     *        and it is not a constructor, apply it to ()
     *  otherwise issue an error
     *  (5) Convert constructors in a pattern as follows:
     *  (5.1) If constructor refers to a case class factory, set tree's type to the unique
     *        instance of its primary constructor that is a subtype of the expected type.
     *  (5.2) If constructor refers to an exractor, convert to application of
     *        unapply or unapplySeq method.
     *
     *  (6) Convert all other types to TypeTree nodes.
     *  (7) When in TYPEmode but not FUNmode or HKmode, check that types are fully parameterized
     *      (7.1) In HKmode, higher-kinded types are allowed, but they must have the expected kind-arity
     *  (8) When in both EXPRmode and FUNmode, add apply method calls to values of object type.
     *  (9) If there are undetermined type variables and not POLYmode, infer expression instance
     *  Then, if tree's type is not a subtype of expected type, try the following adaptations:
     *  (10) If the expected type is Byte, Short or Char, and the expression
     *      is an integer fitting in the range of that type, convert it to that type. 
     *  (11) Widen numeric literals to their expected type, if necessary
     *  (12) When in mode EXPRmode, convert E to { E; () } if expected type is scala.Unit.
     *  (13) When in mode EXPRmode, apply a view
     *  If all this fails, error
     */
    protected def (Typers.this.global.Tree,Int,Typers.this.global.Type)Typers.this.global.Treeadapt(Typers.this.global.Treetree: Typers.this.global.TreeTree, Intmode: IntInt, Typers.this.global.Typept: Typers.this.global.TypeType): Typers.this.global.TreeTree = Typers.this.global.Treetree.=> Typers.this.global.Typetpe Typers.this.global.Treematch {

    /** <p>Check that</p>
     *  <ul>
     *    <li>all parents are class types,</li>
     *    <li>first parent class is not a mixin; following classes are mixins,</li>
     *    <li>final classes are not inherited,</li>
     *    <li>
     *      sealed classes are only inherited by classes which are
     *      nested within definition of base class, or that occur within same
     *      statement sequence,
     *    </li>
     *    <li>self-type of current class is a subtype of self-type of each parent class.</li>
     *    <li>no two parents define same symbol.</li>
     *  </ul>
     */

    /** Given a set `rawSyms' of term- and type-symbols, and a type `tp'.
     *  produce a set of fresh type parameters and a type so that it can be 
     *  abstracted to an existential type.
     *  Every type symbol `T' in `rawSyms' is mapped to a clone.
     *  Every term symbol `x' of type `T' in `rawSyms' is given an
     *  associated type symbol of the following form:
     *
     *    type x.type <: T with <singleton>
     *
     *  The name of the type parameter is `x.type', to produce nice diagnostics.
     *  The <singleton> parent ensures that the type parameter is still seen as a stable type.
     *  Type symbols in rawSyms are fully replaced by the new symbols.
     *  Term symbols are also replaced, except when they are the term
     *  symbol of an Ident tree, in which case only the type of the
     *  Ident is changed.
     */

        val Typers.this.global.Namename = Typers.this.global.Nameif (Typers.this.global.Symbolsym.=> BooleanisType) Typers.this.global.Symbolsym.=> Typers.this.global.Namename else (String)Typers.this.global.NamenewTypeName(Typers.this.global.Symbolsym.implicit scala.Predef.any2stringadd : (Any)scala.runtime.StringAddname(String)java.lang.String+java.lang.String(".type")".type")
        val Typers.this.global.Typebound = Typers.this.global.Symbolsym.=> Typers.this.global.TypeexistentialBound
        val Typers.this.global.Symbolsowner = Typers.this.global.Symbolif ((Typers.this.global.Symbol)BooleanisRawParameter(Typers.this.global.Symbolsym)) => Typers.this.Contextcontext.=> Typers.this.global.Symbolowner else Typers.this.global.Symbolsym.=> Typers.this.global.Symbolowner
        val Typers.this.global.Symbolquantified: Typers.this.global.SymbolSymbol = (Typers.this.global.Symbol)Typers.this.global.Symbolrecycle(Typers.this.global.Symbolsowner.(scala.tools.nsc.util.Position,Typers.this.global.Name)Typers.this.global.TypeSymbolnewAbstractType(Typers.this.global.Symbolsym.=> scala.tools.nsc.util.Positionpos, Typers.this.global.Namename))
